  "text": "Since different lubricant types play a notable role [CITATION_1] on bearing performance, it is general practice to take up more than one lubricant [CITATION_2] ; thus, in order to form a general overview, in this work simulations are performed for three lubricants: SAE 30, SAE 50, and SAE 70 (Fig. 4(c) ). The analysis is based on the fact that unused lubricant is pumped in and emerges to atmosphere, therefore inlet and exit oil pressure values are decided to be 300 kPa and 100 kPa, respectively. Divers inlet oil temperatures are frequently coincided within the literature ([8À12]), to encompass the most recurrent ones into interest the research scope is widened with two oil inlet temperatures: 258C (Fig. 4(d) ) and 758C. ",
